data.title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Rare Air
data.description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Rare Air pays homage to the original 1985 design with a contemporary twist, blending classic elements with modern updates. This iteration features a white leather base complemented by neutral grey collars and overlays, reminiscent of the OG "Storm Blue" colorway. Deep royal blue accents on the ankle flaps and outsole inject a vibrant touch, while the wear-away black Swooshes reveal a layer of red beneath, adding a dynamic and customizable aspect to the sneaker’s aesthetic.

Notable design details include alternating "Air Jordan" and "Nike Air" lettering on the Wings logos, offering a unique nod to the brand’s heritage. The muslin midsole enhances the vintage-inspired look, making this pair a must-have for collectors and new enthusiasts alike.

Released on April 5, 2025, the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Rare Air was available at a retail price of $180.

data.title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 SD Metallic Series Crystal Pink Cream
Nike SB Dunk Low Fog
data.description:
The Nike Dunk SB Low Fog is a skateboarding sneaker that slightly resembles the Nike Dunk SB High Fog released in 2005. Designed to provide individuals with the comfort they need while skateboarding, this sneaker features a black suede upper contrasted with a gray leather Nike Swoosh logo on its side and a grey Nike SB branding on its heel. It also features a mesh tongue, black laces, a dark midsole, a black rubber sole, and a gum rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk SB Low Fog was released in 2021. Originally, it had a retail price of $100.
